(93, 1, '2018-07-10 11:31:56', '2018-07-10 11:31:56', '\n	<p>FAQ</p>\n	<p>Shipping</p>\n	<ul>\n		<li><a href="#dales_faq_1" target="_self"></a><h3>Do I need a permit for my dumpster?</h3 ><p></p></li><li><a href="#dales_faq_2" target="_self"></a><h3>How much space do I need for my dumpster?</h3 ><p></p></li>	</ul>\n	<p>Ordering</p>\n	<ul>\n		<li><a href="#dales_faq_3" target="_self"></a><h3>Do I need to be home for delivery/pickup?</h3 ><p></p></li><li><a href="#dales_faq_2" target="_self"></a><h3>How much space do I need for my dumpster?</h3 ><p></p></li><li><a href="#dales_faq_8" target="_self"></a><h3>Can I cancel my container?</h3 ><p></p></li><li><a href="#dales_faq_9" target="_self"></a><h3>Why can’t I schedule a delivery time?</h3 ><p></p></li>	</ul>\n	<p>Containers</p>\n	<ul>\n		<li><a href="#dales_faq_4" target="_self"></a><h3>What items can not go into my dumpster?</h3 ><p></p></li><li><a href="#dales_faq_5" target="_self"></a><h3>What size dumpster do I need?</h3 ><p></p></li><li><a href="#dales_faq_6" target="_self"></a><h3>How do you open the door on the dumpster?</h3 ><p></p></li><li><a href="#dales_faq_7" target="_self"></a><h3>What to do if someone else fills my container?</h3 ><p></p></li>	</ul>\n	<p><strong>Q: Do I need a permit for my dumpster?</strong></p>\n<p>In general, most cities do not require a permit to place a container on private property. Some cities do require permits for placement in the street or right of way. Permits can be obtained from your city building department or public works department. It is the customers responsibility for obtaining a permit if required.</p>\n	<p><strong>Q: How much space do I need for my dumpster?</strong></p>\n<p>In general, most cities do not require a permit to place a container on private property. Some cities do require permits for placement in the street or right of way. Permits can be obtained from your city building department or public works department. It is the customers responsibility for obtaining a permit if required.</p>\n	<p><strong>Q: Do I need to be home for delivery/pickup? </strong></p>\n<p>In general, most cities do not require a permit to place a container on private property. Some cities do require permits for placement in the street or right of way. Permits can be obtained from your city building department or public works department. It is the customers responsibility for obtaining a permit if required.</p>\n	<p><strong>Q: What items can not go into my dumpster? </strong></p>\n<p>A: The following items are prohibited in all containers:</p>\n<p>• hazardous waste,<br />\n• flammable liquids<br />\n• wet paint (all paint must be dried. We suggest using kitty litter)<br />\n• aerosol cans<br />\n• propane tanks<br />\n• tires<br />\n• medical waste or medications<br />\n• asbestos<br />\n• all liquids including, but not limited to: oils, antifreeze, chemical products, fertilizers<br />\n• hardfill materials, unless in a designated container(dirt, brick, block, concrete, or asphalt)</p>\n<p>If you are unsure of a particular item please contact one of our customer service representatives.</p>\n	<p><strong>Q: What size dumpster do I need? </strong></p>\n<p>A: If you are unsure of the proper size for your project, please refer to container sizes with helpful suggestions for each size container. If you are still unsure, contact one of our customer service representatives and we will help match you with the right sized container for your project.</p>\n	<p><strong>Q: How do you open the door on the dumpster? </strong></p>\n<p>A: We have attached video examples of how to open and close different container doors.</p>\n	<p><strong>Q: What to do if someone else fills my container? </strong></p>\n<p>A: Contents of container are the customers responsibility while in their possession. Customer is responsible for ensuring container remains level and free of prohibited items.</p>\n	<p><strong>Q: Can I cancel my container? </strong></p>\n<p>A: All orders must be cancelled 24 hours prior to delivery for a full refund. Dale’s must confirm cancellation. Orders cancelled same day will incur a $25 cancellation fee if the container is not already in route. If a container is already in route or refused at delivery, customer will incur a $125 dry run fee.</p>\n	<p><strong>Q: Why can’t I schedule a delivery time? </strong></p>\n<p>A: Due to the nature of the work, we are unable to schedule specific delivery times. Factors such as inclement weather, traffic, landfill wait time, and unforeseen issues with previous loads can all affect delivery times. We will do our best to honor your AM or PM requests, but we are unfortunately unable to guarantee delivery times.</p>\n	<p>Contact</p>\n<p>Phone<br />\n586-778-1919</p>\n<p>Email<br />\nsales@dalesdisposal.com</p>\n', 'FAQ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'faq', '', '', '2018-07-10 12:31:22', '2018-07-10 12:31:22', '', 0, 'http://dales.wemes.com.ua/?page_id=93', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(94, 1, '2018-07-10 11:31:56', '2018-07-10 11:31:56', '	<p>Company</p>\r\n	<p>Serving the Tri-County area for over 40 years</p>\r\n	<p>Dale’s started in the wood and landscaping industry with Dale’s Landscape Supply, Inc., dedicated to providing the finest quality and largest selection of landscaping materials available. In 2004 Dale’s expanded into the disposal industry with roll off containers and rubber wheel dumpster trailers. Dale’s Disposal provides 10, 20, 30 and 40 yd roll-off containers, 10 and 20 yard trailers and compactors to support the needs of contractors as well as residents in their efforts with construction, remodeling, demolishing or clean-up projects. Dale’s Disposal can also service industrial and commercial locations with permanent disposal service and has the flexibility to accommodate any pickup schedule. All of the Dale’s Disposal drivers are courteous and professional. Our drivers are in clean uniforms and drive clean, new equipment. Dale’s Disposal drivers have the experience to service your facility or residence and are conscious of their surroundings. Our dispatch manager is in communication with our drivers at all times for improved efficiency and service. Our experienced, knowledgeable staff is committed to keeping both our commercial and retail customers satisfied. We take pride in providing prompt, efficient service to all of our customers, and look forward to continued growth in the tradition of Dale’s.</p>\r\n	<p>Contact</p>\r\n<p>Phone<br />\r\n586-778-1919</p>\r\n<p>Email<br />\r\nsales@dalesdisposal.com</p>\r\n', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '93-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-10 11:31:56', '2018-07-10 11:31:56', '', 93, 'http://dales.wemes.com.ua/2018/07/10/93-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
